This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   Resume a crashed agent session on the bim-ai repo implementing WP-A annotation tools. The session was resuming from a prior crash with the following explicitly stated priorities:
   - **Priority 1 (A1/A2)**: Wire text and leader-text annotation tools end-to-end: core element types, plan renderers, grip providers, inspector, tests
   - **Priority 2 (A3)**: Permanent dimension completeness (zero implementation)
   - **Priority 3 (A4-A9)**: Elevate partial annotations to done (persistent element types, grips, inspector, ≥2 tests)
   - **Priority 4 (A10)**: Material tag live layer lookup
   - **Priority 5 (A11)**: Dimension text overrides
   - **Priority 6 (A12)**: North arrow sheet rendering

   The session also had explicit git bookkeeping instructions: pull --rebase before major tasks, commit after each sub-task, do NOT touch stair/ramp/roof/export/phases/structural/groups files.

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - bim-ai: browser-based BIM authoring tool (React + TypeScript + Three.js, Vite, Vitest)
   - Semantic commands: `onSemanticCommand({ type: 'createXxx', ... })` dispatched from PlanCanvas.tsx, sent via `applyCommand()` POST to `/api/models/{id}/commands`
   - Element types: defined in `packages/core/src/index.ts` (ElemKind union + large Element discriminated union)
   - Rendering primitives: `detailComponentsRender.ts` has `extractDetailComponentPrimitives()` which produces typed primitives; PlanCanvas.tsx renders them via Three.js sprites/lines
   - Grammar state machines: per-tool reducers in `toolGrammar.ts` (e.g., `reduceTextAnnotation`, `reduceLeaderText`)
   - Grip providers: pure functions in `plan/grip-providers/` implementing `ElementGripProvider<E>` interface; registered in `index.ts`'s `gripsFor()` dispatch
   - Auto-commit hooks: git pre-commit hooks automatically commit staged changes when `git add` + `git commit` is run; Prettier also runs PostToolUse after Edit/Write
   - Stale git index: mtime divergence causes false "modified" reports; fix with `git update-index --refresh`

3. Files and Code Sections:
   - **packages/core/src/index.ts**
     - Added `| 'leader_text'` to `ElemKind` union (near line 368)
     - Added `leader_text` Element union member after `annotation_symbol`:
       ```typescript
       | {
           /** ANN-16 — view-local leader annotation: arrow line + optional elbow + text block. */
           kind: 'leader_text';
           id: string;
           hostViewId: string;
           anchorMm: XY;
           elbowMm?: XY;
           textMm: XY;
           content: string;
           arrowStyle?: 'arrow' | 'dot' | 'none';
